# Hostify - Host from Anywhere

**Turn old PCs into production servers with one line of code.**

Host applications from old PCs or home machines using Cloudflare Tunnels. No port forwarding, no dynamic DNS, just pure simplicity.

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/hostify.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/hostify)
[![Python](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/hostify.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/hostify/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

---

## üöÄ Quick Start

```python
from hostify import Host

# Host your app in one line
Host(domain="app.example.com", port=3000).serve()
```

That's it! Your app is now live at `https://app.example.com` with automatic HTTPS.

---

## üì¶ Installation

```bash
pip install hostify
```

**Requirements:**
- Python >= 3.9
- Cloudflare account with a domain
- Cloudflare API token ([setup guide](CLOUDFLARE_SETUP.md))

---

## üéØ Features

- ‚úÖ **One-line API** - Simple and intuitive
- ‚úÖ **Automatic HTTPS** - Secure by default via Cloudflare
- ‚úÖ **No Port Forwarding** - Works behind NAT/firewalls
- ‚úÖ **Cross-Platform** - Windows, Linux, macOS
- ‚úÖ **Static Files** - Built-in HTTP server
- ‚úÖ **Existing Servers** - Works with Flask, Node, PHP, etc.
- ‚úÖ **Auto-Cleanup** - Graceful shutdown with Ctrl+C
- ‚úÖ **Auto-Recovery** - Restarts on connection issues

---

## üñ•Ô∏è CLI Usage

Hostify also provides a powerful command-line interface for quick hosting:

### Installation

```bash
pip install hostify
```

### Commands

**Host a static site:**
```bash
hostify static ./my-website mysite.example.com
```

**Host an existing server:**
```bash
hostify port 3000 app.example.com
```

**Show version:**
```bash
hostify version
```

**Get help:**
```bash
hostify --help
```

### Environment Setup

Set your Cloudflare API token:

**Windows (PowerShell):**
```powershell
$env:CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN="your_token_here"
```

**Linux/macOS:**
```bash
export CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN="your_token_here"
```

### CLI Examples

**Example 1: Host a static portfolio**
```bash
hostify static ./portfolio portfolio.example.com
```

**Example 2: Host a Flask app running on port 5000**
```bash
# Terminal 1: Start Flask
python app.py

# Terminal 2: Host it
hostify port 5000 flask-app.example.com
```

**Example 3: Host a React development server**
```bash
# Terminal 1: Start React dev server (usually port 3000)
npm start

# Terminal 2: Host it
hostify port 3000 react-app.example.com
```

